Engineer, Release Engineering
New York, NY, United States and 1 more

JOB DESCRIPTION
Job Purpose

The Engineer, Release Engineering is responsible for software builds and releases, which includes the design, development, support of builds, scripts, and installation procedures.

 

Responsibilities

Respond to and assist in production operations in a 24/7 environment
Provide support and training to Operations, Development, QA and other team members
Daily Support and Administration of Kubernetes Clusters throughout Development, QA , and Production environments
Collaborate with development teams to construct use case-based Helm Charts for container deployments
Collaborate with development teams to construct use case based Terraform Plans to cloud deployments
Design pipelines for reliable builds & releases to ensure streamlined deployments as part of the overall SDLC
Participate in a weekly on-call rotation for after-hours support
Provide technical analysis, resolve problems, and propose solutions
Take initiative, detail oriented, and demonstrates excellent verbal, written, and interpersonal communications skills
Willingness to learn new and emerging technologies and implement in a short time
Ability to multi-task and manage tasks with varying priorities
Ability to work in a fast paced, team-based environment
 

Knowledge and Experience

3+ years working as a Software Development Engineer or Tools Automation or similar role
Bachelor's Degree or equivalent work experience in software engineering discipline
Familiarity with source control systems (Git, SVN)
Demonstrates top-tier analytics and problem solving
Experience working in a service-oriented team environment
Project Management, organization, and time management
Understand Continuous Integration and Delivery concepts
Experience with one or more of the following technologies
Linux administration, Windows a plus
Maven/Gradle
Jenkins or Jenkins X, including provisioning access, Jenkins Pipelines or working with Jenkins Agents
Scripting languages like Bash, Ruby, Groovy, PowerShell scripting, and Python
Creation of Docker Containers
Setup and configuration of Kubernetes
Design of Terraform Plans or Helm Charts
 

